data("iris")

plt1

#Exercise 1c,1d,1e

plt2<-ggplot(data=iris,mapping=aes(x=Sepal.Length,y=Sepal.Width))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Species, shape = Species))+geom_smooth(method = 'lm')+geom_smooth(method='lm',se=TRUE,color="green")+geom_smooth(aes(col = Species), method='lm', se=TRUE, fullrange=FALSE)+ geom_smooth(method='loess', color='black')
  
plt2
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

#Exercise 1f

plt3<-iris %>% bind_rows(iris) %>% ggplot(aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width, color = Species, shape=Species)) + 
  geom_point() +  geom_smooth(method = 'lm') + facet_wrap(facets =~ Species, scales='free') + theme_bw()

plt3
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

#Exercise 3d

mycols <- rainbow(nrow(starwars))
starwars$gender[starwars$gender == 'masculin'] <- 'blue'
starwars$gender[starwars$gender == 'feminine'] <- 'pink'
ggplot(starwars, aes(x = gender, color=gender)) + geom_bar(fill='white') +
labs(title = "Gender distribution of the sw Universe") +  scale_fill_manual(name = 'Gender', values = as.character(starwars$gender)) + scale_color_manual(values = c('blue', 'red'))

#Exercise 3f

str2 <- starwars %>% drop_na()
str2 %>% ggplot(aes(x=height, color= gender)) +
  geom_density(aes(y=..density..))
